title: Good Driver, Bad driver
text:
We are grateful to have received Islam as our driver. He got us to our hotel safe and politely.

However we had an “original driver” that we “locked  in” with and exchanged texts.

He apparently did not read the texts— did not know where we were standing and the when we did find ea other, it appears he hadn’t read that I was with a man because he waved off my husband and zoomed away despite the fact that I’d sent him a description of us. He then dropped our ride. This was plate #DS73201.

Thanks again for the app and Islam. (Tho I like the option to select or type in location rather than the pin drop— when you’re in a diff city it’s hard to find it— that’s Ubers job!)

Thanks-

title: Very smart way to rip off ppl cents and dollars at a time
text: The Uber service is without doubt one that is really necessary. However, I find that the practice of quoting one price and then in the end being charged more is becoming too frequent. I’ve been charged for wait time when I’m literally there waiting to be picked up and no driver but some how they know how to make it seem as if they r waiting for you. I’ve always been charged for wait time when I have been asked by the driver to meet them at a particular door because it’s more convenient for them and then it turns out that I had them waiting when in truth it’s they who had me waiting. Not to mention the road charges for routes that incur tolls or other stupid charges. Total rip off and you don’t know about this until u c the charge come up on your account!
